title: NATO Says It Will Invite Ukraine Some Day, Resisting Calls to Act Soon
description: The alliance firmed up its plans to include Ukraine eventually, but gave no timetable, siding with President Biden and frustrating some East European members.

title: Finnish Right-Wing Party Leader Apologizes After Racist Posts Surface
description: Riikka Purra, who leads the nationalist Finns party, was the second member of her faction to come under fire for offensive comments since the government was formed a month ago.

title: BBC Crisis Grows as Staff Member Is Accused of Abuse by 2nd Person
description: The British broadcaster was facing questions about its handling of an internal inquiry over explicit photos after another person accused the male staff member of sending abusive messages over a dating app.

title: Biden Administration Is Quietly Debating Whether to Send Ukraine ATACMS Missiles
description: The United States already has plans for its limited stock of long-range Army Tactical Missile Systems.

title: When Climate Change Hits Home
description: A dispatch from the flooded house of our new lead writer.

title: Vetoes in U.N. Security Council Imperil Cross-Border Humanitarian Aid to Syria
description: Dueling resolutions failed on Russian- and U.S.-led vetoes, cutting off a cross-border lifeline from Turkey to more than four million people.

title: Rikkie Valerie Kollé Is the First Trans Woman to Win Miss Netherlands
description: Rikkie Valerie Kollé, 22, will represent the Netherlands at the 72nd annual Miss Universe pageant in El Salvador later this year.

title: Yoweri Museveni, Ugandan President, and Son Are Accused of Crimes Against Humanity
description: Testimonies sent to the International Criminal Court detail accusations of torture and abuse committed against hundreds of victims before and after the elections in 2021.

title: Erdogan’s U-turn On Sweden Could Signal Warming of Ties With the West
description: Long seen as an in-house disrupter in NATO, President Recep Tayyip Erdogan of Turkey could be scaling back his close ties with Russia.

title: Vermont Floods Show Limits of America’s Efforts to Adapt to Climate Change
description: The lack of a comprehensive national rainfall database and current flood maps hampers the ability to prepare for storms intensified by climate change.

title: Japan’s Supreme Court Lifts Restroom Restriction at Work for Trans Woman
description: The decision represents some forward momentum in L.G.B.T.Q. rights in Japan, which lags behind other G7 nations in extending them.

title: Will Turkey Become a Member of the EU? Here’s What to Know.
description: As part of his U-turn on unblocking Sweden’s bid for NATO membership, President Recep Tayyip Erdogan of Turkey appears to have received vague promises about changing his country’s strained relationship with the European Union.

title: An English Brewery Overseen by Monks
description: At Mount Saint Bernard Abbey, the monks help make Britain’s only Trappist beer, a full-bodied brew that has won fans since its launch five years ago.

title: Russia-Ukraine War: NATO Leaders Gather for Summit, Buoyed by Turkey’s Support for Sweden’s Membership
description: Turkey’s abrupt shift enables the alliance to focus on Ukraine’s possible path to membership, and on continuing support for Kyiv. President Volodymyr Zelensky is expected to arrive for the summit later on Tuesday.

title: The Global Immigration Backlash
description: Left-leaning parties in both Europe and the U.S. are often out of step with public opinion on immigration.

title: ‘Heaviest Rain Ever’ in Southern Japan Sets Off Floods and Landslides
description: Unusually heavy rain on the mountainous island of Kyushu has killed at least six people and left three others missing.

title: Protests Erupt in Israel as Government Takes Step to Rein In Judiciary
description: Demonstrators caused widespread disruption after the governing coalition moved forward with plans to limit the power of the Supreme Court.

title: As Ukraine’s Counteroffensive Inches Forward, Soldiers Face What Russians Left Behind
description: As Ukrainian troops inch forward in the counteroffensive, they are occupying positions abandoned by enemy troops. Says one: “It’s not very pleasant.”

title: Rising Heat Underground Is Sinking Chicago Ever So Slightly
description: Basements and train tunnels constantly leak heat, causing the land to sink and straining building foundations. Scientists call it “underground climate change.”

title: Omdurman, Sudan, Becomes Center of New Phase of War
description: Fierce fighting has erupted in the city of Omdurman, across the Nile from the capital, Khartoum, in a desperate battle to control supply routes.

title: North Korea Threatens Actions Against American Spy Planes
description: The country warned that it would shoot down American spy planes, escalating verbal attacks on the U.S. as South Korea’s leader traveled to attend a NATO summit.

title: Your Tuesday Briefing
description: A breakthrough on Sweden’s accession to NATO.

title: Iceland Monitors New Volcanic Eruption
description: Larger eruptions have disrupted European air travel, but officials said this small one, in an uninhabited area that until recently had been dormant for centuries, posed no immediate risks.

title: Biden Bets High-Level Diplomacy Can Cool Fiery Relations With China
description: President Biden hopes the diplomatic trips this summer by his aides lead to frank talks with Xi Jinping and other Chinese officials before the 2024 U.S. elections.
